parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Whining noise when accelerating
turning
and slowing down
loss of power steering
stiff steering wheel
difficulty turning the wheel
loud grinding noise
and leaking power steering fluid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a potential problem with the airbag system, which can lead to a failure to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
sometimes intermittently
and may be accompanied by a warning message or chime.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag fails to deploy in a crash
sometimes accompanied by a warning light or message on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent airbag issues can lead to a failure to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates intermittently
or the airbag system malfunctions intermittently
sometimes accompanied by a warning message or chime.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, shake, or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or shakes violently
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power or speed
the transmission makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or fail, leading to a loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails
the timing chain breaks or fails
the engine makes unusual noises
the vehicle loses power or speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine overheats
the water pump leaks or fails
the coolant level drops
the vehicle loses power or speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle rolling backward or forward on inclines can cause a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls backward or forward on inclines
the vehicle is difficult to control on hills
the vehicle requires quick movements from brake to accelerator.
